concept_explanation.naive:
**Naive pattern matching O(nm):**

```java
// Check every position in text
for (int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++) {
    int j;
    for (j = 0; j < m; j++)
        if (text.charAt(i+j) != pattern.charAt(j)) break;
    if (j == m) result.add(i); // match at i
}
// Worst case: text='aaaa...a', pattern='aaab' → O(nm)
```

concept_explanation.kmp:
**KMP: skip positions using failure function:**

```java
// Step 1: Build LPS (Longest Proper Prefix that is also Suffix)
// lps[i] = length of longest proper prefix of pattern[0..i] that is also suffix
// pattern = 'AABAAB'
// lps =    [0,1,0,1,2,3]
//  pattern[0]='A': no proper prefix → lps[0]=0
//  pattern[1]='A': 'A'='A' → lps[1]=1
//  pattern[2]='B': 'AB'≠'AB' but 'A'≠'B' → lps[2]=0
//  pattern[3]='A': 'A'='A' → lps[3]=1
//  pattern[4]='A': 'AA'='AA' → lps[4]=2
//  pattern[5]='B': 'AAB'='AAB' → lps[5]=3

// Step 2: Search using LPS to skip redundant comparisons
// When mismatch at j: don't restart from i+1
// Instead: j = lps[j-1] (skip already-matched prefix)
```

worked_example.final_code:
// Build LPS:
int[] lps = buildLPS(pattern);
// KMP search:
int i=0, j=0;
while(i < text.length()) {
    if(text.charAt(i)==pattern.charAt(j)) { i++; j++; }
    if(j==m) { result.add(i-m); j=lps[j-1]; }
    else if(i<n && text.charAt(i)!=pattern.charAt(j)) {
        if(j>0) j=lps[j-1]; else i++;
    }
}
